"><h2 id=3D"regular-polygon-formulas-for-area-perimeter-angles-and-radius">=
Regular polygon formulas for area, perimeter, angles, and radius</h2>
<div class=3D"textBlock"><p>To calculate any regular polygon area, perimete=
r, or radius, we only need to know the number of sides (polygon shape) and =
its side length. To calculate the angles, only the number of sides is neces=
sary.</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p><strong>Area formula for a regular polygon</strong></p>
<p><code>area =3D n =C3=97 a=C2=B2 =C3=97 cot(=CF=80/n) / 4 </code></p>
<p>where:</p>
<ul>
<li><code>n</code> =E2=80=94 number of sides; and</li>
<li><code>a</code> =E2=80=94 side length.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<p>If you have doubts about the units of area, look at our <a href=3D"https=
://www.calctool.org/conversion/area-converter" class=3D"js-link">area conve=
rter</a>.</p>
<ol start=3D"2">
<li>
<p><strong>Perimeter</strong></p>
<p><code>perimeter =3D n =C3=97 a</code></p>
</li>
</ol>
</div><picture class=3D"imageBlock__image-align--right" style=3D"width: 36%=
;"><source media=3D"only screen and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and=
 (max-width: 800px)" type=3D"image/webp" srcset=3D"https://uploads-cdn.omni=
calculator.com/images/n-gon-all.png?width=3D748&amp;enlarge=3D0&amp;format=
=3Dwebp"><source media=3D"(max-width: 800px)" type=3D"image/webp" srcset=3D=
"https://uploads-cdn.omnicalculator.com/images/n-gon-all.png?width=3D374&am=
p;enlarge=3D0&amp;format=3Dwebp"><source media=3D"only screen and (-webkit-=
min-device-pixel-ratio: 2)" type=3D"image/webp" srcset=3D"https://uploads-c=
dn.omnicalculator.com/images/n-gon-all.png?width=3D850&amp;enlarge=3D0&amp;=
format=3Dwebp"><source type=3D"image/webp" srcset=3D"https://uploads-cdn.om=
