les and incircle and circumcircle radii" class=3D"imageBlock" loading=3D"la=
zy" width=3D"100%"></picture><div class=3D"textBlock"><ol start=3D"3">
<li>
<p><strong>Interior (=CE=B1) and exterior (=CE=B2) angles</strong> :</p>
<ul>
<li><code>=CE=B1 =3D (n - 2) =C3=97 =CF=80/n</code>;</li>
<li><code>=CE=B2 =3D 2 =C3=97 =CF=80/n</code></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Incircle radius (apothem)</strong></p>
<p><code>r=E1=B5=A2 =3D a/[2 =C3=97 tan(=CF=80/n)]</code></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Circumcircle radius</strong><br>
<code>r=EA=9C=80 =3D a/[2 =C3=97 sin(=CF=80/n)]</code></p>
</li>
</ol>
<p>Our regular polygon calculator uses all those equations. With these form=
ulas, you can calculate regular triangles, squares, and many more shapes.</=
p>
